This paper is primarily focused on the implementation of a parallel version of Coalgebraic Logic Programming (CoALP), which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the coalgebraic semantics of logic programming, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of parallelism and corecursion, which are concepts related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of CoALP in the programming language Go, which is a popular language for software engineering (cs.SE).
